# Testing Guidelines

## Test Requirements
- Write tests for all new functionality
- Use pytest and Home Assistant's test helpers
- Mock external API calls in tests
- Test both success and failure scenarios
- Maintain test coverage above 80%

## Test Structure
- Mock Meraki SDK calls in tests
- Test both success and failure scenarios
- Test configuration flows
- Test entity creation and updates
- Test error handling paths

## Pre-commit Checks
- Run tests before committing
- Run linting (Black, flake8, mypy)
- Ensure all tests pass
- Check test coverage

## Integration Testing
- Test integration in actual Home Assistant instance
- Verify device discovery works correctly
- Test configuration flows
- Validate sensor data accuracy
